OL,3,CCompany fined #200k after worker
OL,4,Csuffers burns to face and body in
OL,5,Cexplosion
OL,7,FHSE inspector Tim Nicholson said:
OL,8,F"This incident could so easily have
OL,9,Fbeen avoided by properly planning the
OL,10,Ftask, ensuring that all workers
OL,11,Finvolved were suitably competent and
OL,12,Fmaking sure that electrical conductors
OL,13,Fwere isolated before the work began.
OL,15,F"Companies should be aware that HSE
OL,16,Fwill not hesitate to take appropriate
OL,17,Fenforcement action against those that
OL,18,Ffall below the required standards."
